# NLTK: Natural Language toolkit Processing library for tokenizing, stemming, tagging, parsing, and semantic reasoning.
# N-GRAM: Help us to understand the context of a word by looking at the words that come before and after it. N-grams are a contiguous sequence of n items from a given sample of text or speech. The items can be phonemes, syllables, letters, words or base pairs according to the application. The n-grams typically are collected from a text or speech corpus.
# Pandas: Python Data Analysis Library working with structured data. It provides data structures and functions needed to manipulate structured data seamlessly.
# Pandas-DataFrame: A 2-dimensional labeled data structure with columns of potentially different types. You can think of it like a spreadsheet or SQL table, or a dict of Series objects. It is generally the most commonly used pandas object.
# Matplotlib: Library for creating static, animated, chart, and interactive visualizations in Python. It is a multi-platform data visualization library built on NumPy arrays and designed to work with the broader SciPy stack.
# NER: Named Entity Recognition is to locate and classify the essential pieces of information named entities into pre-defined categories such as person names, organizations, locations, etc.
# NER used rules and machine learning to identify named entities in text.
